Subject: Re: [T2] cv joints, clunk, clunk

CV's will usually only make noise when pressure is allied, so when you push
in on the clutch, you take away the pressure, thus relieving the stress on
the CV's.  Sounds like you have one or more bad CV's.

> Hey, I have a clunk, clunk, when I am accelerating, but goes away when I
> disengage the clutch.  CVs would still make noise, right?  What could it be?
> Throw out bearing?  Loose pressure plate bolt?  Thanks for your time.  Joel
> Lambert, 74 westy, Atmore, Alabama
